{"article_id":"0heQruSCrWFTZdKt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As America anxiously awaits the release of the so-called \" Nunes memo \"","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"- a four-page document","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"written by Rep. Devin Nunes","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"( R-CA )","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"alleging","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"that the FBI fraudulently snooped on a Trump campaign adviser -","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"it ' s worth keeping in mind that there isn ' t just one memo in play here .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"The first is the original Nunes memo .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"The second memo ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"written by Rep. Adam Schiff","depth":12},{"id":10,"text":"( D-CA ) ,","depth":12},{"id":11,"text":"is a rebuttal to Nunes ' s attacks on the FBI .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"The third memo is actually an edited version of Nunes ' s original memo ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"which he sent to the Trump administration for review .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"The reason","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"there are three memos","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"is because Nunes ' s first memo was flawed","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"- on this point , there ' s consensus .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"The debate is over whether it was flawed fundamentally","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"( Schiff ' s position )","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"or in minor ways","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"that required very light edits","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"( if you believe Nunes ) .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"Either way , the existence of three memos is seriously complicating the Republican campaign to # ReleaseTheMemo","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"- an effort","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"that ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"if successful ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"could have profound implications for special counsel Robert Mueller ' s investigation into Trump ' s Russia ties and the FBI ' s independence more broadly .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Most of what we know about the first Nunes memo ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"which has been circulated around the House of Representatives","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"but remains classified ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"comes from press accounts of its contents .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"According to a New York Times report","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"published on January 28 ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Nunes ' s memo focuses on surveillance of Carter Page , a Trump campaign foreign policy adviser with business ties to Russia and open sympathies with the Kremlin ' s foreign policy .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"Page went to Moscow in July 2016","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"while he was serving on the Trump campaign , a move","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"that raised eyebrows among the FBI agents","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"investigating the Trump team ' s ties to Russia .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"So the FBI and Department of Justice put together an application to a Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"( FISA )","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"court","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"- a court","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that approves surveillance warrants","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"pertaining to national security and foreign intelligence -","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"to start watching Page .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"The court granted the application in the fall of 2016 ,","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"giving the FBI the green light .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"The memo reportedly alleges","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"that this surveillance was not properly vetted by the court ;","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"specifically , that it relied on the now-infamous Steele dossier , the document","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"prepared by former British spy Christopher Steele","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"alleging the existence of a conspiracy between Donald Trump and the Russian government .","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"The dossier ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"partially and indirectly funded by the Clinton campaign ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"is the one","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"alleging , among other things , the existence of the so-called \" pee tape . \"","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"\" The memo ' s primary contention , \"","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"the Times writes ,","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"\" is that FBI and Justice Department officials failed to adequately explain to an intelligence court judge","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"in initially seeking a warrant for surveillance of Mr . Page","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"that they were relying in part on research by [ Steele ] . \"","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"What ' s more , the Nunes memo reportedly says","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"that Deputy Attorney General Rod Rosenstein signed off on an application","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"to renew the surveillance of Page in the spring of 2017 .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"This would imply","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that Rosenstein either overlooked the FBI and DOJ ' s reliance on the Steele dossier ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"which Republicans see as a partisan hack job ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"or acquiesced to it .","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"Blaming Rosenstein is a big deal ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"as he ' s currently in charge of supervising Mueller ' s Russia probe","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"- and President Trump has reportedly mused in private about firing him .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Experts on the FBI and surveillance policy say","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"the Nunes memo ' s arguments ,","depth":7},{"id":74,"text":"at least as summarized in press accounts ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"are extremely dodgy .","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"The sheer number of people across the Department of Justice","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"who would need to be either deeply incompetent or involved in a conspiracy ,","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"they say ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"makes its assertions exceptionally hard to believe .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"Nonetheless , Republicans have been pushing for its release ,","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"arguing","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"that there really is a scandal this big","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"and the public deserves to know about it .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"On Monday night , the House Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"( HPSCI )","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"- which Nunes chairs -","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"voted for the memo ' s public release .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Every Republican on the committee voted in favor of it ;","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"every Democrat voted against it .","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"To hold the vote ,","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"Nunes invoked an extremely obscure part of the House Standing Rules ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"which govern the legislative body ' s operation","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"- specifically , Clause 11 of Rule X .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"Clause 11 allows HPSCI to disclose classified information , like the Nunes memo ,","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"if \" the public interest would be served by such disclosure . \"","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"Clause 11 has never been invoked before .","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"In theory , Monday ' s vote should set up a five-day maximum deadline for the memo ' s release .","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"The only thing","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"that can block it","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"is a note from the president","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that the memo ' s release would damage national security .","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"If Trump did send such a notification ,","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"it would require a vote from the entire House , not just the HPSCI ,","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"to overrule him .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"But it ' s hard to imagine Trump blocking the memo ' s release ,","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"given his long-running allegations of FBI bias against him .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"The New York Times suggests","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"that Trump plans to give HPSCI the go-ahead","depth":7},{"id":110,"text":"to release the memo on Friday ,","depth":7},{"id":111,"text":"but nothing has been officially confirmed .","depth":5},{"id":112,"text":"Democrats wrote a counter-memo","depth":4},{"id":113,"text":"- but it ' s unlikely to see the light of day","depth":4},{"id":114,"text":"Rep. Schiff , the ranking Democratic member on HPSCI , has been the biggest critic of the Nunes memo .","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"He argued in a Monday press conference","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"that the document is an attempt","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"to \" politicize the intelligence process \" in service of a \" deeply flawed person in the Oval Office . \"","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"Schiff has compiled his objections to the Nunes memo into another classified document","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"let ' s call it the Schiff memo .","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"The 10-page note ,","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"according to Schiff and other Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"is a detailed rebuttal to the claims in Nunes ' s memo .","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"He reportedly defends the FBI ' s FISA application on Page","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"and says","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"that there was no deception surrounding the Steele dossier .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"It also ,","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"per CNN ,","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"attacks Nunes ' s political motivations","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"- arguing","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"that the entire thing is a sham","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"designed to aid Trump ' s attack on the FBI .","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"The Republicans on House Intelligence , so far , have decided not to release Schiff ' s memo .","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"On Monday night , Schiff submitted to release his memo alongside the Nunes memo under the Clause 11 procedures .","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"He was defeated in another party-line vote .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"A Schiff spokesperson told me","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"they still hope to release their memo .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"To address Republican concerns","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"that it may compromise intelligence sources ,","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"Schiff \" will send his memo for review by appropriate agencies , \"","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"the spokesperson said .","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"as things stand ,","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"that won ' t happen right now .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"HPSCI Republicans believe","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"that the Nunes memo ,","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"which","depth":14},{"id":148,"text":"the FBI has publicly said","depth":14},{"id":149,"text":"leaves out vital contextual information ,","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"is something","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"the public needs to see","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"- while the Democratic memo","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"defending the bureau with additional context","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"is not .","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"This isn ' t so much about allowing the public to make up its mind , then ,","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"as it is about Republicans advancing a very specific allegation of anti-Trump bias at the FBI","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"- one","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"that the president has been pushing publicly for months .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"The third memo complicates all of this substantially","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"- and may explain","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"why the first memo has yet to be released .","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"Late on Wednesday night , Schiff sent out a tweet","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"alleging","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"that Nunes had \" secretly altered \" his memo","depth":12},{"id":165,"text":"before sending it to the White House for vetting .","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"The changes ,","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"per Schiff ,","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"were \" substantive \" and \" material \"","depth":12},{"id":169,"text":"-","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"meaning that it was , effectively , not the same memo","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"that HPSCI voted to release on Monday night .","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"That would make it illegal to release the altered memo ,","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"Schiff argued ,","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"without a new Clause 11 vote .","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"It ' s not clear how valid the legal reasoning is here","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"- again , Clause 11 has never been used before .","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"But setting that aside ,","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"it ' s not clear what the changes actually were .","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"Schiff ' s tweet didn ' t lay out their specific nature ,","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"other than to say","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"they \" do not correct the profound distortions and inaccuracies \" in the original document .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"Instead , we ' ve had a war of anonymous sources in the press .","depth":10},{"id":183,"text":"One Republican source told the Washington Post","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"that the only changes were \" two edits","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"requested by the FBI and by the minority \"","depth":14},{"id":186,"text":"and some other minor things , like grammar corrections .","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"A Democratic source contested this ,","depth":12},{"id":188,"text":"telling the Post","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"that the changes were an attempt","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"to \" water down some of the majority ' s assertions \"","depth":15},{"id":191,"text":"and that the Republicans needed to \" restart the process in a transparent manner . \"","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"So it ' s possible the edits weren ' t very important .","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"It ' s possible","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"they correct major errors .","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"It ' s also possible they were direct responses to the Schiff rebuttal memo","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"designed to address its criticisms .","depth":12},{"id":197,"text":"We still don ' t know how this memo business is going to be resolved .","depth":8},{"id":198,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"if Trump does , in fact , clear the way","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"for the memo to be released on Friday ,","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"it raises a clear question :","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"Is he approving the original Nunes memo or the edited one","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"that Nunes transferred to him ?","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"And","depth":12},{"id":205,"text":"if so ,","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"are there major differences ,","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"as Schiff alleges ?","depth":14},{"id":208,"text":"The most unclear story in Washington just got a little more confusing .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":417,"left":292,"right":416,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":292,"left":280,"right":291,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":236,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":231,"right":235,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":214,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":0,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":211,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":1,"right":210,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":212,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":230,"left":6,"right":229,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":220,"right":228,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":7,"right":219,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":219,"left":217,"right":218,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":217,"left":216,"right":11,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":216,"left":8,"right":215,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":223,"right":227,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":221,"right":222,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":221,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":222,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":224,"right":226,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":224,"left":18,"right":19,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":20,"right":225,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":225,"left":21,"right":22,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":23,"right":234,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":24,"right":233,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":25,"right":232,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":26,"right":27,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":279,"left":255,"right":278,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":239,"right":254,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":239,"left":238,"right":31,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":238,"left":28,"right":237,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{